sect3.screen:
&cmdline;cat Makefile
foo: foo.c gcc -o foo foo.c
&cmdline;

sect3.para:
Another invocation of &make; (or make all)
does nothing. This is because none of the files that &make;
looks at have been modified.

sect3.screen:
&cmdline;make all
make: Nothing to be done for `all'.
&cmdline;

&cmdline;make clean
rm -f hw main.o hello.o world.o
&cmdline;
